{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down canonical defer-reason format string with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f2b676cf7096499ae","f538987c52fd60a5c"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"canonical defer-reason format string"},{"coaching":"Plan how block_threshold values across criteria_routing.json will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f92ed52c1eae4d1b3","f0ee940eb4a286cf2"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"block_threshold values across criteria_routing.json"},{"coaching":"Pin down defer-reason output for DET-tier findings with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["ffd60656fd5786c0d","f9c2105b3f6220aa2","f93e3d41a435efad4"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"defer-reason output for DET-tier findings"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] ticket title vs. implementation mechanism alignment will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa9ab9973d660112d"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"ticket title vs. implementation mechanism alignment"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on triage_advisories failure modes on malformed findings: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["ff20ced7a273d0d19"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"triage_advisories failure modes on malformed findings"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":7,"blocking":0,"dropped":12,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":6,"ran":true,"references":6,"resolved":3,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":3},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":7794,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":7,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":92,"verify_lint_abstained":91},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1964,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["G6","T8"],"floored_finding_ids":["ffd60656fd5786c0d","ff20ced7a273d0d19"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":410.6,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":606798.9,"total_ms":607402.6,"verify_requests":25},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5a","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the exact defer-reason format string in the plan (e.g., `f\"deferred: priority {priority:.2f} is {gap:.2f} below its {block_threshold:.2f} block line\"`) so the AC's 'locked format' claim is verifiable independently of the implementer's choice.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line` — given as an example, not a formal pattern","AC1: 'every `reason` string matches the locked format' — but 'locked format' is not formally specified (no f-string, no regex, no stated decimal precision)","Absence: no explicit format string like `f\"deferred: priority {priority:.2f} is {gap:.2f} below its {block_threshold:.2f} block line\"` appears in the plan"],"finding":"The defer-reason format is specified by example only (`deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line`), not as a formal format string or regex. The determinism AC checks that `reason` matches the 'locked format', but the plan never formally defines what 'locked' means (decimal precision, exact wording, f-string template). A solo executor writes both the format and its test, creating circular validation — two independent agents could produce non-identical formats that each pass their own tests while differing from each other.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2b676cf7096499ae","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"What > Mechanism choice > Defer reason bullet; AC1 (determinism proving command)","norm_id":"n2477251f9c6efc28","priority":0.469,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor chooses 4 decimal places instead of 2; the test they write passes, but the format differs from what reviewers/R7 expects","The gap calculation is rounded vs truncated — indeterminate from the example alone"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add to the 'Defer reason' bullet: `Format string (normative): f\"deferred: priority {priority:.2f} is {gap:.2f} below its {block_threshold:.2f} block line\"` — where `gap = block_threshold - priority`, values rounded to 2 decimal places.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace the illustrative defer-reason example with a canonical format string (e.g., `f\"deferred: priority {priority:.2f} is {gap:.2f} below its {block_threshold:.2f} block line\"` where `gap = block_threshold - priority`) so both the implementor and the AC1 test author have an unambiguous contract to implement and verify against.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'Built only from the finding's own numbers, e.g. `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line` — fixed words + recorded numbers, no LLM prose, non-prescriptive.'","AC1 quote: 'every `reason` string matches the locked format (only fixed tokens + recorded numeric fields — no LLM/prescriptive prose)'","The word 'e.g.' signals the format string is illustrative, not canonical — no regex or f-string template is given anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The defer-reason format is specified only by a single illustrative example (`deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line`) rather than a canonical format string. The AC says 'every reason string matches the locked format (only fixed tokens + recorded numeric fields)' and the proving test must verify format conformance — but 'the locked format' is never stated as a Python f-string, regex, or token grammar. An implementor and a test author have no specification to falsify against: formats like `priority=0.32 falls 0.28 short of threshold 0.60`, or varying decimal precision, all satisfy 'fixed tokens + recorded numeric fields' without matching the illustrated example.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f538987c52fd60a5c","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Defer reason' paragraph; AC1 (determinism proving command)","norm_id":"nf34ae57ce5b83cb9","priority":0.469,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test author writes `-k determinism` tests using a regex like `r'deferred: priority [0-9.]+ is [0-9.]+ below its [0-9.]+ block line'` — the test passes or fails depending on the regex they choose, not a shared canonical format.","Two implementors independently produce different format strings (e.g. differing number of decimal places or word 'threshold' vs 'block line') — both claim to implement the spec, and there is no arbiter."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the 'Defer reason' paragraph, add: 'Exact template: `f\"deferred: priority {priority:.2f} is {gap:.2f} below its {block_threshold:.2f} block line\"` where `gap = round(block_threshold - priority, 2)`. Two decimal places, no rounding of intermediate values.' The AC1 proving test then asserts against this exact regex or f-string evaluation.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify that `block_threshold` varies per criterion in `criteria_routing.json` (ranging from 0.60 to 0.95) — replace 'the 0.60 via plan-review's routing' with 'the per-criterion value from criteria_routing.json (e.g. 0.60 for F1/E2/COH/G6, up to 0.95 for most overlay criteria)', and update the defer-reason example to use a different numeric pair or label it as criterion-specific.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'block_threshold is present on LLM-decided findings (resolved by decide.py; 0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing, not decide.py's 0.95 DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)'","criteria_routing.json: F1=0.60, E2=0.60, COH=0.60, G6=0.60 — but G1G2=0.70, E4=0.75, T4=0.70, T8=0.70, T1=0.70, E1/E3/E5/E6/G5/T5a-e/T2/T3/T6/T7/T9/T10/T11/T12/T13/T14=0.95","The defer-reason example in the plan uses '0.60' as the block line — will only be accurate for a subset of criteria-findings"],"finding":"The plan states 'block_threshold … 0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing' as if 0.60 is the plan-review block_threshold value — but criteria_routing.json contains a range of per-criterion thresholds (F1/E2/COH/G6 = 0.60; G1G2 = 0.70; E4 = 0.75; T4/T8/T1 = 0.70; many others = 0.95). The phrase misleadingly implies 0.60 is THE value from the routing rather than one criterion-specific value. This is load-bearing: the defer-reason example ('deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line') hard-codes 0.60, and a test author following that example could accidentally pin 0.60 as a constant in boundary or ordering tests rather than using the per-finding value.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f92ed52c1eae4d1b3","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'The ranking rule' subsection: \"block_threshold is present on LLM-decided findings (resolved by decide.py; 0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing\"","norm_id":"n96bf5b41ce19652d","priority":0.198,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test author follows the defer-reason format example using 0.60 and writes a test that pins 0.60 as a literal rather than reading the per-finding field — the test passes for F1/E2 findings but is wrong for E4/G1G2 findings.","A code reviewer reading the plan misunderstands the triage as comparing against a constant 0.60 routing value rather than each finding's own recorded block_threshold."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Change: '0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing, not decide.py's 0.95 DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD'\nTo: 'the per-criterion value from criteria_routing.json (0.60 for F1/E2/COH/G6; 0.70–0.95 for most other criteria), not decide.py's 0.95 DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD'\n\nAnd update the defer-reason example to make clear the number is the finding's own recorded block_threshold, not a routing constant.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the '0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing' claim to clarify that 0.60 is one of several per-criterion thresholds (alongside 0.70, 0.75, 0.95) and that `triage_advisories` reads the value recorded on each decided finding — illustrate the boundary AC with multiple representative threshold values (e.g., 0.60, 0.95) rather than implying 0.60 is universal.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'block_threshold is present on LLM-decided findings (resolved by decide.py; 0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing, not decide.py's 0.95 DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)'","criteria_routing.json shows block_threshold values: 0.6 (F1, E2, T1, ISF, …), 0.7 (multiple), 0.75 (one criterion), 0.95 (majority of criteria) — not a uniform 0.60","AC2 (boundary bucketing) parametrizes the test but does not specify which threshold value to use as the test's block_threshold, leaving the implementor to infer — the '0.60' claim is a likely source of confusion here"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'block_threshold … 0.60 via plan-review's criteria_routing.json routing' as a representative ground truth for LLM-decided findings, but `criteria_routing.json` contains at least eight distinct block_threshold values (0.60, 0.70, 0.75, 0.95, etc.) across criteria — 0.60 is not the universal or default LLM-finding threshold. The design itself is correct (triage reads `f.get('block_threshold', DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)` from the decided finding), but the illustrative claim is an unverified capability assertion that could mislead test implementors who write boundary tests assuming 0.60 as the canonical LLM-finding threshold.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0ee940eb4a286cf2","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What — The ranking rule (fully specified, grounded in real fields)","norm_id":"n4d48b6db0bdf6efa","priority":0.198,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test author writes boundary AC2 tests with `block_threshold=0.60` as the canonical LLM value, but a finding whose criterion has `block_threshold=0.95` is treated differently — the test passes vacuously for the wrong reason.","Documentation derived from this plan perpetuates the incorrect '0.60 is the plan-review LLM threshold' claim."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace the parenthetical with: 'block_threshold is present on LLM-decided findings (resolved by decide.py; varies by criterion — e.g. 0.60 for F1/E2, 0.95 for most others — so triage_advisories reads it as f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD), and AC2 should parametrize tests over at least two distinct threshold values)'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the ticket title with the actual implementation mechanism — either retitle to something like 'R6: advisory-triage coaching stage (Pass-4, ship-first)' or add a one-line note at the top of the 'What' section flagging that the name 'coaching move' is metaphorical and not a MOVE_REGISTRY entry.","cohort":["E3","G5","T6"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title: 'advisory-triage coaching move (pass-4 registry, ship-first)'","Plan body: 'It is NOT an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY … So the triage is a small pure function on the plan-review Pass-4 path'"],"finding":"The ticket title says \"pass-4 registry\" but the plan body explicitly and correctly explains the implementation is NOT via the MOVE_REGISTRY — the title signals the wrong mechanism and could cause an implementing agent to search the registry path first.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa9ab9973d660112d","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title: 'R6: advisory-triage coaching move (pass-4 registry, ship-first)'; Mechanism choice section","norm_id":"n23f0e76318cfe8e6","priority":0.1886,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementing agent reads the title, navigates to `MOVE_REGISTRY` / `review_kernel/coach.py`, and begins implementing a registry entry before reading the body's correction — wasting time or producing the wrong artifact."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Rename to 'R6: advisory-triage coaching stage (Pass-4 path, ship-first)' and/or add at the top of the 'What' section: 'Note: despite the name ","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend the `boundary` or `advisory_only` parametrized test) that asserts the output `block_threshold` for a DET-tier advisory (where the finding carries no `block_threshold` field) equals `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD` (0.95), confirming the resolved-fallback value appears in the triage entry.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'DET-tier advisories stamped by partition_findings … do not carry it, so triage_advisories reads it as f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)'","Output schema declares 'block_threshold: float' as always-present in the triage entry","No AC checks the value of block_threshold in the triage output for DET-tier advisories"],"finding":"The plan specifies that for DET-tier advisories, `triage_advisories` resolves `block_threshold` via `f.get('block_threshold', DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)` (yielding 0.95) and includes it in the output struct, but no AC pins the output `block_threshold` value for DET-tier findings — leaving the described output contract (resolved vs. raw field value) untested.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9c2105b3f6220aa2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What → output shape / The ranking rule (DET-tier block_threshold fallback); AC set (no covering criterion)","norm_id":"n5538870b78f3595e","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A DET-tier advisory appears in the surviving set; the triage output carries block_threshold=0.4 (wrong) instead of 0.95 (the resolved default); the defer reason calculation is correct but the output schema field is silently wrong — no test catches it."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend the `advisory_only` or `boundary` parametrized test fixture to include one DET-tier advisory (no `block_threshold` field) and assert `triage_entry[\"block_threshold\"] == DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD` (0.95).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a unit-test AC (or extend `advisory_only` / `boundary`) that passes a DET-tier advisory fixture without a `block_threshold` field and asserts it buckets as `defer` with the correct `block_threshold` value (0.95) reflected in the `reason` string.","cohort":["E5"],"criteria":["E5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'DET-tier advisories stamped by `partition_findings` (`orchestrator.py`) do **not** carry it, so `triage_advisories` reads it as `f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)` — the 0.95 default applies when absent … under which a DET advisory (priority 0.4) buckets `defer`.'","No AC references DET-tier findings or the `block_threshold`-absent branch.","The five ACs cover: determinism, boundary (uses explicit block_threshold), ordering, advisory-only filter, integration — none specify a fixture without `block_threshold`."],"finding":"The plan explicitly specifies that DET-tier advisory findings lack a `block_threshold` field and that `triage_advisories` must fall back to `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD` (0.95) via `f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)`, causing those advisories to bucket as `defer` (priority 0.4 < 0.95 - 0.10 = 0.85). This is a distinct, named code path described in the mechanism section, but no AC exercises it — none of the five unit-test ACs mention DET-tier findings or the missing-`block_threshold` fallback.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f93e3d41a435efad4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria / `tests/unit/test_plan_review_triage.py`; plan section 'The ranking rule (fully specified)'","norm_id":"n06f406fa927fef91","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A DET-tier finding (no `block_threshold`) is passed to `triage_advisories`; if the fallback is accidentally omitted or uses the wrong constant, all five ACs could still pass while this path is broken.","A future refactor renames `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD` without updating `triage_advisories`; no test catches the regression."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `test_plan_review_triage.py`, add a parametrized case to the boundary or a new `-k det_tier` test: construct a finding dict with `decision='advisory'`, `priority=0.4`, **no** `block_threshold` key, and assert `bucket == 'defer'` and `reason` contains `'0.95'` (the DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD). This pins the fallback behavior and guards against accidental removal of `f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)`.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Since APPLY_NOW_MARGIN is explicitly expected to be tuned by R7 dogfood results, expose it as a configurable setting (e.g., via the existing plan-review config/settings object or an env var) rather than a bare module constant, or explicitly state in the plan that a code-change tuning cycle is acceptable and why.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN is a named module constant, default 0.10'","'validated post-ship by dogfooding via R7's advisory-application-latency metric'","No mention of a config file, env var, or settings object for this threshold"],"finding":"APPLY_NOW_MARGIN (0.10) is introduced as a named module constant that the plan explicitly ties to R7 tuning feedback, meaning it is expected to evolve post-ship — yet the plan provides no config-file or environment-variable mechanism for changing it without a code edit and redeploy.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7b4b02c64d10fb67","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py` — `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN` constant; Why section: 'validated post-ship by dogfooding via R7's advisory-application-latency metric'","norm_id":"nf6961097d66778ad","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["R7 dogfood data shows 0.10 is too tight or too loose; tuning requires a code change, PR, review cycle, and redeploy rather than a config push.","Future reviewers cannot distinguish 'intentionally hardcoded' from 'forgot to make configurable' without reading the full plan context."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a one-liner to read from the plan-review settings/config object with a fallback: `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN = settings.get('apply_now_margin', 0.10)`. If the settings object is not appropriate here, document in the plan that the constant is intentionally locked until R7 data is reviewed, at which point a single-line PR changes it — making the decision explicit rather than implicit.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the rationale: `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` is re-exported by `rebar.llm.review_kernel` (its `__init__.py`), not by `orchestrator.py` — update the 'Mechanism choice' paragraph to avoid a misleading import path for the implementer.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["orchestrator.py line 87: `from .passes import MOVE_REGISTRY, load_move_registry` — only these two symbols are re-exported","review_kernel/__init__.py lines 35-44: `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` is re-exported there, not in orchestrator.py","plan text: 'The registry schema (`review_kernel/coach.py` `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA`) is a *per-finding* `{subject}`-placeholder template the LLM fills; a single `{subject}` substitution cannot express a ranked two-bucket split across all surviving advisories. So the triage is a small pure function on the plan-review Pass-4 path — blast radius stays inside plan-review; the shared kernel coach mechanism and its notes are unchanged.'"],"finding":"The plan states that `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` (from `review_kernel/coach.py`) is 're-exported by `orchestrator.py`', but `orchestrator.py` only re-exports `MOVE_REGISTRY` and `load_move_registry` from `passes.py` — it does NOT re-export `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA`. The schema is re-exported by `review_kernel/__init__.py`. This factual slip in the rationale could mislead an implementer who tries to import `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` from `orchestrator` (which would fail at runtime) rather than from `review_kernel` or `review_kernel.coach`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f74e7f92da3a5f048","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'Mechanism choice (rationale)' paragraph: 'in `passes.py`, re-exported by `orchestrator.py`'","norm_id":"n18f6d667a23afb4a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer following the plan's re-export claim tries `from rebar.llm.plan_review.orchestrator import MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` and gets an ImportError at test or runtime."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change 'in `passes.py`, re-exported by `orchestrator.py`' to 'in `passes.py`, re-exported by `rebar.llm.review_kernel`' (its `__init__.py`).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"na","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either (a) realign the leaf to implement the feature as a MOVE_REGISTRY entry with the coaching prompt the parent specifies (adapting how the prompt expresses triage guidance without requiring per-finding {subject} substitution), OR (b) update the parent plan's §R6 'What' to approve the pure-function architecture and machine-readable output before re-reviewing this leaf.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (line 205): 'Add a move to the registry (rendered deterministically, like all moves): \"Triage each surviving advisory into the plan before claiming: apply it, or record a one-line deferral rationale in the description (see c8cc's \\'Plan-review remediations\\' section as the exemplar pattern).\"'","Leaf (Mechanism choice section): 'It is NOT an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY… The registry schema (MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA) is a per-finding {subject}-placeholder template the LLM fills; a single {subject} substitution cannot express a ranked two-bucket split across all surviving advisories. So the triage is a small pure function…'","Leaf (Output shape section): 'The stage produces a structured triage array… attached to the returned verdict as a top-level key verdict[\"triage\"]'","MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA in src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py confirms the template must carry a single {subject} placeholder — but this constraint is the leaf's own justification for diverging, not the parent updating the parent to permit the divergence."],"finding":"The leaf's core mechanism directly contradicts the parent's specified mechanism: the parent (§R6, line 205) says 'Add a move to the registry (rendered deterministically, like all moves)' and prescribes a specific author-facing coaching prompt string; the leaf explicitly rejects this — 'It is NOT an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY' — and instead delivers a standalone pure function emitting a machine-readable JSON `verdict[\"triage\"]` array. This changes the architectural artifact (registry entry → pure function), the output form (coaching prompt → structured JSON), and the audience (author prompt → agent-facing data structure), all without updating the parent first.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd4dc21ddb0225675","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf: 'Mechanism choice (rationale)' section; Parent: docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md §R6, line 205","norm_id":"n795b4acb622658a1","priority":0.088,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer following the leaf adds a pure function + JSON output; an implementer following the parent adds a MOVE_REGISTRY entry with a coaching string. These are architecturally incompatible deliverables that cannot both be 'correct'.","The parent's A/B falsifiability experiment ('the move is deterministic to toggle') depends on a MOVE_REGISTRY entry being togglable — the leaf's pure function that always runs is not toggleable via the registry's applicability filter mechanism.","The parent's coaching prompt targets the author ('Triage each surviving advisory into the plan before claiming'); the leaf's JSON array targets the agent/system. These are different intervention points for the same latency problem."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Preferred path (b): amend the parent's §R6 'What' to read: 'Add a deterministic triage stage (implemented as a pure function, not a MOVE_REGISTRY entry, because the registry's per-finding {subject} template cannot express a cross-finding two-bucket sort) that partitions surviving advisories into apply-now / defer buckets and attaches the result to verdict[\"triage\"] for agent consumption.' Then re-review this leaf against the updated parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a minimum-advisory-count guard to `triage_advisories` (or its call site) matching the parent's N≈5 threshold, or update the parent plan to explicitly drop the count condition and explain why unconditional triage is preferable.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (line 205): 'Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive on a passing review (N≈5).'","Leaf (Eligibility bullet): 'Only findings with decision == \"advisory\" are triaged.' — no count guard.","Leaf (What section): no mention of a minimum advisory count before triage runs.","ABSENCE: no N threshold constant or conditional in the leaf's proposed passes.py implementation."],"finding":"The parent specifies a count-based attach trigger — 'Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive on a passing review (N≈5)' — but the leaf drops this threshold entirely: `triage_advisories` runs unconditionally on all surviving advisory findings regardless of count, including when there is only one advisory. This is a deliverable the parent implies should be conditional that the leaf makes unconditional.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fecd9bb34e931afe3","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf: 'Eligibility' bullet and 'Scope / passes.py' description; Parent: docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md §R6, line 205 ('Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive… N≈5')","norm_id":"nf71b2993be3394e4","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A review with a single low-priority advisory (e.g. priority 0.2) produces a triage array with one 'defer' entry — noise for the author and agent, where the parent would have stayed silent.","The parent's falsifiability experiment ties the A/B toggle to a count condition; without the N threshold the triage fires on every review, making the toggle semantics differ from the parent's design."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a module constant `TRIAGE_MIN_ADVISORIES = 5` in passes.py and return an empty list from `triage_advisories` when `len(surviving) < TRIAGE_MIN_ADVISORIES`, matching the parent's 'N≈5' intent. Document the constant in the AC and in docs/plan-review-gate.md.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1","COH"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The Scope section declares 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' as a deliverable, but no AC verifies that the bespoke orchestrator path actually sets verdict[\"triage\"] — the integration AC only exercises the plan_review_coach step via workflow_ops.py.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc19e5a047566bf67","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity') vs AC5 ('drives the plan_review_coach step with fixture findings')","norm_id":"nbba12f3707251a4e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add an AC: 'Parity: the bespoke orchestrator path also sets verdict[\"triage\"] equal to triage_advisories(surviving); a test drives that path with the same fixture findings and asserts the triage array matches. Proving command: pytest tests/unit/test_plan_review_triage.py -k orchestrator_parity -q.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan's Scope section refers to updating 'the bespoke orchestrator path ... symmetrically for parity,' but the bespoke _run_passes/coach path was retired in epic solid-timer-unison (WS1). No separate live bespoke coach path exists in orchestrator.py — the only active coach path runs through the workflow step `plan_review_coach` in workflow_ops.py. This edit target is either ghosted (refers to retired code) or unresolvably ambiguous.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f88815b375def9bf1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section: 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity'","norm_id":"nd4be0324fd0b0e4d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Remove the clause 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' from Scope, since the only active coach assembly path is workflow_ops.plan_review_coach. If parity with recovery paths is intended, call that out explicitly (see next finding).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The docs AC proving command (`grep -q \"APPLY_NOW_MARGIN\" ... && grep -q \"apply-now\" ...`) checks only two string tokens but the AC text requires the documentation to cover four distinct items: the triage stage, the ranking rule (APPLY_NOW_MARGIN default AND ordering), the defer-reason format, and the R7 dogfood expectation — the command would pass if only APPLY_NOW_MARGIN and 'apply-now' appear anywhere in the file.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6c596c8276b4933c","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — docs AC: '`grep -q \"APPLY_NOW_MARGIN\" docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q \"apply-now\" docs/plan-review-gate.md`'","norm_id":"n2fe276add7d02e29","priority":0.165,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace with: `grep -q 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'apply-now' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'deferred: priority' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'R7' docs/plan-review-gate.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The docs AC proving command (`grep -q 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' ... && grep -q 'apply-now' ...`) verifies only two string presences but the AC prose requires documenting four additional items: the ordering rule, the defer-reason format, and the R7 dogfood expectation — the command silently passes even if those are absent from the doc.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff02f553b91e80f73","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — 'docs/plan-review-gate.md documents…' bullet and its Proving Command","norm_id":"nda1a1fd5a0792ba3","priority":0.165,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace the single proving command with: `grep -q 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'apply-now' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'deferred: priority' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'R7' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'criteria\\[0\\]' docs/plan-review-gate.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan asserts 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' but the Scope section does NOT list orchestrator.py or the bespoke passes.py:pass4_coach entry point as a file to be changed. The bespoke path (passes.py:pass4_coach → review_kernel.coach, called by orchestrator.py) is a separate call site from workflow_ops.py:plan_review_coach, and has its own verdict-assembly flow. Without an explicit scope entry for it, the symmetry claim is unverifiable from the plan — and if the bespoke path is not updated, the triage array will silently be absent on runs through that path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffac0b48dcb311134","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity') vs. Scope section (lists only passes.py, workflow_ops.py, tests, docs)","norm_id":"ncfecbe746b802e8a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Scope section, add an entry for the bespoke path: e.g., 'src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py or passes.py:pass4_coach — invoke triage_advisories on the surviving advisory findings and attach the result to the verdict before returning, symmetric with the workflow_ops path.' Also add a corresponding integration AC that drives the bespoke path.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The Scope says 'the bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity' but never names the file or function. Code confirms the bespoke path is `passes.pass4_coach` (in `passes.py`) — but `passes.py` is listed in Scope only for `triage_advisories` and `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN`, not for modifying `pass4_coach`. No AC verifies the bespoke path sets `verdict['triage']`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f12875d15a8e1f695","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('bespoke orchestrator path is updated symmetrically for parity') / `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py:839` (`pass4_coach`)","norm_id":"nc3c1c3af8a53208a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit note to the 'Defer reason' paragraph clarifying that for DET-tier findings (which lack a `block_threshold` field), the value used in the reason string is `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD` (0.95), and that the AC1 test must include a DET advisory fixture (no `block_threshold` field) whose expected reason uses 0.95.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan quote: 'Built only from the finding's own numbers, e.g. `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line` — fixed words + recorded numbers, no LLM prose'","Plan quote (mechanism section): 'DET-tier advisories stamped by `partition_findings` (`orchestrator.py`) do **not** carry it, so `triage_advisories` reads it as `f.get(\"block_threshold\", DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)` — the 0.95 default applies when absent'","orchestrator.py line 412-424: DET advisory findings dict has no `block_threshold` key — confirmed by reading partition_findings source","The 'Defer reason' description and the 'ranking rule' mechanism description are co-located but contradictory: one says 'finding's own numbers', the other says '0.95 default applies when absent'"],"finding":"The plan states the defer-reason is 'built only from the finding's own numbers' — but for DET-tier advisory findings, `block_threshold` is NOT a field on the finding dict (confirmed: `partition_findings` in orchestrator.py stamps DET advisories with only `priority=0.4`, `validity`, `impact`, `severity`, `tier='DET'`, and `decision='advisory'`, with no `block_threshold` key). The triage function resolves this via `f.get('block_threshold', DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)` (0.95), which is correct, but the fallback value (0.95) is NOT 'the finding's own number' — it's a module constant injected at read time. The plan's 'Defer reason' section says 'only fixed tokens + recorded numeric fields', which is not literally true for DET advisory findings where block_threshold comes from the module constant, not from a field recorded on the finding.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffd60656fd5786c0d","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'The ranking rule' paragraph and 'Defer reason' paragraph; orchestrator.py partition_findings (lines 412-424)","norm_id":"n68da92d864850e6c","priority":0.198,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test author for AC1 writes a fixture DET advisory finding (no block_threshold field) and expects the reason string to contain '0.95' — but if they read only the 'Defer reason' description and not the mechanism section, they may incorrectly set block_threshold=0.60 on the fixture.","The AC1 determinism test passes with block_threshold=0.95 on the fixture but the implementor omits the f.get fallback, causing the function to raise KeyError on live DET findings."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that `triage_advisories` wraps its core logic in a try/except (returning `[]` on any error) so that a failure in the triage stage never propagates to fail `plan_review_coach` and never causes coaching loss — consistent with the existing defensive pattern in `workflow_ops.py` (operator-attested enrichment).","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan states: 'invoke triage_advisories on the surviving advisory findings and set verdict[\"triage\"] before the closing validate_structured(verdict, _OUTPUT_SCHEMA) return' — no exception handling specified","workflow_ops.py line 434-436: operator_attested enrichment is wrapped in try/except with 'best-effort enrichment; never fail the gate on it' comment — the established pattern for a pure helper that must not fail the step","gate_dispatch.py _recover_plan_review_coach_failure: recovers from any coach-step failure by dropping coaching entirely — meaning a triage bug causes coaching loss, not just triage loss","ABSENCE: no 'try/except' or 'fail-safe' language around triage_advisories in the plan"],"finding":"The plan does not specify failure-mode behavior for `triage_advisories` itself raising an exception. If a malformed finding (e.g. `criteria` is `None`, `priority` is a non-numeric string) causes `triage_advisories` to raise inside `plan_review_coach`, the exception propagates and causes the entire coach step to fail, triggering `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` — which drops all coaching output, not just the triage key. This is a disproportionate blast radius for a pure sorting/bucketing function, and it is inconsistent with the rest of `plan_review_coach`'s defensive posture (operator-attested enrichment is wrapped in `try/except` for the same reason). The plan should specify that `triage_advisories` wraps its logic in a try/except and returns an empty list on any error, keeping `verdict[\"triage\"] = []` or omitting the key, so the coach step always succeeds.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff20ced7a273d0d19","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Scope: workflow_ops.py' bullet; also the Mechanism section describing injection before validate_structured","norm_id":"n8f0e49435627a587","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A finding produced by a future code path has `priority` set to a non-numeric value (e.g. a string from a schema-lenient deserialization); `float(f.get('priority', 0.0))` raises TypeError inside `triage_advisories`; the entire `plan_review_coach` step fails; the recovery path assembles a DEGRADED verdict with empty coaching.","A DET-tier advisory finding is missing the `criteria` key entirely (None); the sentinel guard for `criteria[0]` raises AttributeError; same cascade."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Scope / workflow_ops.py bullet, add: 'wrap the `triage_advisories` call in a try/except that logs a warning and falls back to `verdict[\"triage\"] = []` (or omits the key), so a triage failure never propagates to fail the coach step.' In passes.py, the function itself should similarly guard against malformed field types (non-numeric priority, non-list criteria) rather than letting them propagate.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"6c2911b2adadc8d1","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":410.6,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":606798.9,"total_ms":607402.6,"verify_requests":25},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"5dac-c177-56ff-4af4","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"43d1545237745f4666dcc13c81587c824251e51d"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784256038400161001,"uuid":"6f37595e-254b-4a64-85c4-02388eae933b"}